question: Which biomarkers are associated with the biomarker alias "ARGININE/SERINE-RICH" with the description "From NCBI Gene: microRNAs (miRNAs) are short (20-24 nt) non-coding RNAs that are involved in post-transcriptional regulation of gene expression in multicellular organisms by affecting both the stability and translation of mRNAs. miRNAs are transcribed by RNA polymerase II as part of capped and polyadenylated primary transcripts (pri-miRNAs) that can be either protein-coding or non-coding. mi
query: SELECT * FROM biomarker AS biomarker JOIN biomarker_alias AS biomarker_alias ON biomarker.id = biomarker_alias.biomarker_internal_id WHERE biomarker_alias.alias = "arginine/serine-rich" and biomarker.biomarker_description = "From NCBI Gene: microRNAs (miRNAs) are short (20-24 nt) non-coding RNAs that are involved in post-transcriptional regulation of gene expression in multicellular organisms by affecting both the stability and translation of mRNAs. miRNAs are transcribed by RNA polymerase II as part of capped and polyadenylated primary transcripts (pri-miRNAs) that can be either protein-coding or non-coding. miRNAs bind to complementary sequences in the 3' UTR of multiple target mRNAs, usually silencing the targeted mRNA.  miRNAs may trigger the cleavage of their target molecules or act as translational repressors. miRNAs are thought to target approximateley 60% of all genes and are able to repress hundreds of targets each."

question: What is the id of the disease whose expression has an adjusted p-value of 3.5e-126 and the name "Head and Neck Cancer"?

question: What are the biomarker type and QA state for biomarkers with expression score greater than or equal to 77.9 for the described entity: "Synovial tissue"?
query: SELECT biomarker_edrn.biomarker_type, biomarker_edrn.qa_state FROM biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn JOIN anatomical_entity AS anatomical_entity ON biomarker_edrn.uberon_anatomical_id = anatomical_entity.id JOIN healthy_expression AS healthy_expression ON anatomical_entity.id = healthy_expression.uberon_anatomical_id WHERE anatomical_entity.description = "A thin, loose vascular connective tissue that makes up the membranes surrounding joints and the sheaths protecting tendons (particularly flexor tendons in the hands and feet) where they pass over bony prominences. Synovial tissue contains synovial cells, which secrete a viscous liquid called synovial fluid; this liquid contains protein and hyaluronic acid and serves as a lubricant and nutrient for the joint cartilage surfaces[BTO]. Synovial tissue can be found in tendons (tissues that connect muscle to bone), bursae (fluid-filled, cushioning sacs found in spaces between tendons, ligaments, and bones), and the cavity (hollow enclosed area) that separates the bones of a freely movable joint, such as the knee or elbow[BTO]." and healthy_expression.expression_score = 77.90000

question: Give me the description and key of all disease mutation site annotations which are predicted by the netNGlyc tool on the position 214 in the disease mutation.

question: What is the statistical significance and p-value of the differentials expressed on chromosome 3 for the disease germ cell cancer?

question: Show me the FDA QA status and title for biomarker with description PTPRS, a single-pass type I membrane protein, interacts with LAR-interacting protein LIP.1. PTPRS is a member of the protein tyrosine phosphatase (PTP) family. PTPs are known to be signaling molecules that regulate a variety of cellular processes including cell growth, differentiation, mitotic cycle, and oncogenic transformation. This PTP contains an extracellular region, a single transmembrane segment and two tandem intracytoplasmic catalytic domains, and thus represents a receptor-
query: SELECT biomarker_edrn.biomarker_title, biomarker_edrn.qa_state FROM biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_edrn.id = biomarker.id JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker.id = biomarker_fda.id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_description = "PTPRS, a single-pass type I membrane protein, interacts with LAR-interacting protein LIP.1. PTPRS is a member of the protein tyrosine phosphatase (PTP) family. PTPs are known to be signaling molecules that regulate a variety of cellular processes including cell growth, differentiation, mitotic cycle, and oncogenic transformation. This PTP contains an extracellular region, a single transmembrane segment and two tandem intracytoplasmic catalytic domains, and thus represents a receptor-type PTP. The extracellular region of this protein is composed of multiple Ig-like and fibronectin type III-like domains. Studies of the similar gene in mice suggested that this PTP may be involved in cell-cell interaction, primary axonogenesis, and axon guidance during embryogenesis. This PTP has been also implicated in the molecular control of adult nerve repair. PTPRS has been detected in all tissues tested except for placenta and liver." and biomarker_fda.test_submission = "K062744"

question: How many distinct genes symbol does the biomarker description "The GSTT1 gene encodes glutathione S-transferase theta 1, a member of a superfamily of proteins that catalyze the conjugation of reduced glutathione to a variety of electrophilic and hydrophobic compounds. This group of proteins can be subdivided into five main classes: alpha, mu, pi, theta, and zeta. The theta class includes GSTT1 and GSTT2. The GSTT1 and GSTT2 share 55% amino acid sequence identity and both of them were claimed to have an important role in
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker.gene_symbol FROM biomarker AS biomarker WHERE biomarker.biomarker_description = "The GSTT1 gene encodes glutathione S-transferase theta 1, a member of a superfamily of proteins that catalyze the conjugation of reduced glutathione to a variety of electrophilic and hydrophobic compounds.  This group of proteins can be subdivided into five main classes: alpha, mu, pi, theta, and zeta. The theta class includes GSTT1 and GSTT2. The GSTT1 and GSTT2 share 55% amino acid sequence identity and both of them were claimed to have an important role in human carcinogenesis. The GSTT1 gene is located approximately 50kb away from the GSTT2 gene. The GSTT1 and GSTT2 genes have a similar structure, being composed of five exons with identical exon/intron boundaries.  GSTT1 is found in erythrocytes and is expressed at low levels in liver. In lung, it is expressed at low levels in Clara cells and ciliated cells at the alveolar/bronchiolar junction. It is absent from epithelial cells of larger bronchioles."

question: What is the biomarker drugs associated with FDA test submission P980018?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_drug, biomarker_fda.test_submission FROM biomarker_fda_drug AS biomarker_fda_drug JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_fda_id = biomarker_fda.id JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_fda.id = biomarker.id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_description = "The RARB gene encodes the retinoic acid receptor beta.  It is a member of the thyroid-steroid hormone receptor superfamily of nuclear transcriptional regulators (NRB1 class).  These receptors bind to their targets as heterodimers in response to their ligands, all-trans or 9-cis retinoic acid, and regulate gene expression in various biological processes. This receptor localizes to the cytoplasm and to subnuclear compartments where it binds retinoic acid, the biologically active form of vitamin A which mediates cellular signalling in embryonic morphogenesis, cell growth and differentiation. It is thought that the RARB protein limits growth of many cell types by regulating gene expression. There are three distinct RAR subtypes; RARalpha, RARbeta and RARgamma. RARalpha is present in most tissue types, whereas RARbeta and RARgamma expression is more selective.  Two full length transcript variants have been verified.  A third is possible." and biomarker_fda.test_submission = "P980018"

This gene encodes a glutathione S-transferase that belongs to the mu class. The mu class of enzymes functions in the detoxification of electroph
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name, biomarker_fda.test_submission FROM biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda.test_trade_name JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_fda.id = biomarker.id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_description = "From NCBI Gene: Cytosolic and membrane-bound forms of glutathione S-transferase are encoded by two distinct supergene families. At present, eight distinct classes of the soluble cytoplasmic mammalian glutathione S-transferases have been identified: alpha, kappa, mu, omega, pi, sigma, theta and zeta. This gene encodes a glutathione S-transferase that belongs to the mu class. The mu class of enzymes functions in the detoxification of electrophilic compounds, including carcinogens, therapeutic drugs, environmental toxins and products of oxidative stress, by conjugation with glutathione. The genes encoding the mu class of enzymes are organized in a gene cluster on chromosome 1p13.3 and are known to be highly polymorphic. question: Show all biomarkers described as PCSK9, with their anatomical id, that have a pmid different than 23319435
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_edrn.uberon_anatomical_id FROM biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_edrn.id = biomarker.id JOIN biomarker_article AS biomarker_article ON biomarker.id = biomarker_article.biomarker_internal_id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_description = "PCSK9 is a proprotein convertase belonging to the proteinase K subfamily of the secretory subtilase family. PCSK9 is synthesized as a soluble zymogen that undergoes autocatalytic intramolecular processing in the endoplasmic reticulum. It may function as a proprotein convertase, play a role in cholesterol homeostasis, and have a role in the differentiation of cortical neurons. PCSK9 activity is inhibited by EGTA. PCSK9 is expressed in neuro-epithelioma, colon carcinoma, hepatic and pancreatic cell lines, and in Schwann cells. Mutations in the PCSK9 gene have been associated with a third form of autosomal dominant familial hypercholesterolemia." and biomarker_article.pmid != "23319435"

question: What are the feature keys of the disease mutation site annotations whose corresponding disease mutationals have a frequency of 7 and whose prediction probabilities are not 0.479?
query: SELECT DISTINCT disease_mutation_site_annotation.feature_key FROM disease_mutation_site_annotation AS disease_mutation_site_annotation JOIN disease_mutation AS disease_mutation ON disease_mutation_site_annotation.disease_mutation_id = disease_mutation.id JOIN disease_mutation_impact_prediction AS disease_mutation_impact_prediction ON disease_mutation.id = disease_mutation_impact_prediction.disease_mutation_id WHERE disease_mutation.mutation_frequency = 7 and disease_mutation_impact_prediction.probability != 0.479

question: Can you please show all FDA test trials which are class II and whose submission is not K062725?

question: Give the different reference amino acid residues for the disease mutation site in malignant mesothelioma with annotation "ATP; via amide nitrogen and carbonyl oxygen".

question: What are the information about the disease mutation article with pmid 11801303
query: SELECT * FROM disease_mutation_article AS disease_mutation_article WHERE disease_mutation_article.pmid = 11801303

question: Show me the PubMed Ids for biomarker articles with biomarker description 'From NCBI Gene: This gene encodes a member of the serpin superfamily of serine proteinase inhibitors. The encoded protein is localized to the endoplasmic reticulum and plays a role in collagen biosynthesis as a collagen-specific molecular chaperone. Autoantibodies to the encoded protein have been found in patients with rheumatoid arthritis. Expression of this gene may be a marker for cancer, and nucleotide polymorphisms in this gene may be associated with preterm birth caused by preterm premature rupture of membranes. Alternatively spl
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_article.pmid FROM biomarker_article AS biomarker_article JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_article.biomarker_internal_id = biomarker.id JOIN biomarker_alias AS biomarker_alias ON biomarker.id = biomarker_alias.biomarker_internal_id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_description = "From NCBI Gene: This gene encodes a member of the serpin superfamily of serine proteinase inhibitors. The encoded protein is localized to the endoplasmic reticulum and plays a role in collagen biosynthesis as a collagen-specific molecular chaperone. Autoantibodies to the encoded protein have been found in patients with rheumatoid arthritis. Expression of this gene may be a marker for cancer, and nucleotide polymorphisms in this gene may be associated with preterm birth caused by preterm premature rupture of membranes. Alternatively spliced transcript variants have been observed for this gene, and a pseudogene of this gene is located on the short arm of chromosome 9. [provided by RefSeq, May 2011]" and biomarker_alias.alias != "bA317E16.2"

question: What are the distinct PMIDs of disease mutation articles with cosmic data source and whose disease mutation site annotations do not have description "Fructose"?

question: What is the approval status for tests used in the trial with id NCT01891344 that are not Roche Cobas DNA Sample Preparation Kit?

question: List all test submissions for biomarker with id "urn:edrn:bmdb:biomarker:81" which are not submitted in combination with TAFINLAR (dabrafenib) in combination with MEKINIST (trametinib).
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda.test_submission FROM biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_fda.id = biomarker.id JOIN biomarker_fda_drug AS biomarker_fda_drug ON biomarker_fda.id = biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_fda_id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_id = "urn:edrn:bmdb:biomarker:81" and biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_drug != "TAFINLAR(dabrafenib) in combination with MEKINIST (trametinib)"

question: List all site predictions for disease mutations with an "G" at the amino acid position and where the description is not "N5-methylglutamine".
query: SELECT DISTINCT disease_mutation_impact_prediction.site_prediction FROM disease_mutation_impact_prediction AS disease_mutation_impact_prediction JOIN disease_mutation AS disease_mutation ON disease_mutation_impact_prediction.disease_mutation_id = disease_mutation.id JOIN disease_mutation_site_annotation AS disease_mutation_site_annotation ON disease_mutation.id = disease_mutation_site_annotation.disease_mutation_id WHERE disease_mutation.amino_acid_residue_variation = "G" and disease_mutation_site_annotation.description != "N5-methylglutamine"

question: What are the PMIDs of the disease mutation articles which contain a missense mutation with the reference amino acid residue S but for which the description of the disease mutation site annotation is not "Important for activity"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT disease_mutation_article.pmid FROM disease_mutation_article AS disease_mutation_article JOIN disease_mutation AS disease_mutation ON disease_mutation_article.disease_mutation_id = disease_mutation.id JOIN disease_mutation_site_annotation AS disease_mutation_site_annotation ON disease_mutation.id = disease_mutation_site_annotation.disease_mutation_id WHERE disease_mutation.reference_amino_acid_residue = "S" and disease_mutation_site_annotation.description != "Important for activity"

question: List the different trade names of tests that have an FDA approval status of PMA and are used for a disease other than Blastoma.
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_test_use.test_trade_name FROM biomarker_fda_test_use AS biomarker_fda_test_use JOIN biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test ON biomarker_fda_test_use.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name JOIN disease AS disease ON biomarker_fda_test.doid = disease.id WHERE biomarker_fda_test.test_approval_status = "PMA" and disease.name != "blastoma"

question: Which different types of biomarkers are associated with the FDA gene symbol NID2 and that are not submitted as K062695?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_edrn.biomarker_type FROM biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_edrn.id = biomarker.id JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker.id = biomarker_fda.id WHERE biomarker.gene_symbol = "NID2" and biomarker_fda.test_submission != "K062695"

question: What are the distinct NCIt term biomarkers for FDA test submission K062717 and do not have biomarker id 1034 ?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_ncit_term.ncit_biomarker FROM biomarker_fda_ncit_term AS biomarker_fda_ncit_term JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker_fda_ncit_term.biomarker_fda_id = biomarker_fda.id JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_fda.id = biomarker.id WHERE biomarker_fda.test_submission = "K062717" and biomarker.biomarker_id != "urn:edrn:bmdb:biomarker:1034"

question: What are the different test submissions for FDA tests whose origin is "somatic mutation" and whose disease name is not "liver cancer"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_test_use.test_submission FROM biomarker_fda_test_use AS biomarker_fda_test_use JOIN biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test ON biomarker_fda_test_use.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name JOIN disease AS disease ON biomarker_fda_test.doid = disease.id WHERE biomarker_fda_test.biomarker_origin = "somatic mutation" and disease.name != "liver cancer"

question: What are the all the disease mutation articles with PMID 8075649?
query: SELECT * FROM disease_mutation_article AS disease_mutation_article WHERE disease_mutation_article.pmid = 8075649

question: What is the species common name for the gene symbol 1700073E17Rik when the expression is not in gold call quality?
query: SELECT DISTINCT species.species_common_name FROM species AS species JOIN xref_gene_ensembl AS xref_gene_ensembl ON species.speciesid = xref_gene_ensembl.speciesid JOIN healthy_expression AS healthy_expression ON xref_gene_ensembl.ensembl_gene_id = healthy_expression.ensembl_gene_id WHERE xref_gene_ensembl.gene_symbol = "1700073E17Rik" and healthy_expression.call_quality != "GOLD"

question: What are the PMIDs of all the biomarker article corresponding to the biomarker with description "Tetraspanin 13" and whose EDRN title does not contain "SERPINB3"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_article.pmid FROM biomarker_article AS biomarker_article JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_article.biomarker_internal_id = biomarker.id JOIN biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn ON biomarker.id = biomarker_edrn.id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_description = "tetraspanin 13" and biomarker_edrn.biomarker_title != "SERPINB3"

question: What are the different description for biomarkers that are in QA state "Accepted" but does not have the anatomical entity identifier "UBERON:0006083"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker.biomarker_description FROM biomarker AS biomarker JOIN biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn ON biomarker.id = biomarker_edrn.id JOIN anatomical_entity AS anatomical_entity ON biomarker_edrn.uberon_anatomical_id = anatomical_entity.uberon_identifier WHERE biomarker_edrn.qa_state = "Accepted" and anatomical_entity.uberon_identifier != "UBERON:0006083"

question: What are the different types of biomarkers for the anatomical entity Brain Blood Vessels with expression level not low?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_edrn.biomarker_type FROM biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn JOIN anatomical_entity AS anatomical_entity ON biomarker_edrn.uberon_anatomical_id = anatomical_entity.id JOIN healthy_expression AS healthy_expression ON anatomical_entity.id = healthy_expression.uberon_anatomical_id WHERE anatomical_entity.name = "brain blood vessel" and healthy_expression.expression_level_gene_relative != "LOW"

question: What are the expression rank scores of the healthy expressions associated with the "Regional part of the septal nuclei, lying dorsal and slightly lateral to the medial septal nucleus. The lateral septum receives the bulk of projections of areas projecting to the septal nuclei (Adapted from Brodal, 1981)." in stage other than 7 weeks (mouse)?
query: SELECT DISTINCT healthy_expression.expression_rank_score FROM healthy_expression AS healthy_expression JOIN anatomical_entity AS anatomical_entity ON healthy_expression.uberon_anatomical_id = anatomical_entity.id JOIN stage AS stage ON healthy_expression.uberon_developmental_id = stage.id WHERE anatomical_entity.description = "Regional part of the septal nuclei, lying dorsal and slightly lateral to the medial septal nucleus. The lateral septum receives the bulk of projections of areas projecting to the septal nuclei (Adapted from Brodal, 1981)." and stage.name != "7 weeks (mouse)"

question: What are the different stages for the expression score 25.6 for gene symbols other than '1700036O09Rik'?
query: SELECT DISTINCT stage.name FROM stage AS stage JOIN healthy_expression AS healthy_expression ON stage.id = healthy_expression.uberon_developmental_id JOIN xref_gene_ensembl AS xref_gene_ensembl ON healthy_expression.ensembl_gene_id = xref_gene_ensembl.ensembl_gene_id WHERE healthy_expression.expression_score = 25.60000 and xref_gene_ensembl.gene_symbol != "1700036O09Rik"

question: List the different test design for the FDA test named "NCT01260168" for diseases other than "parathyroid carcinoma".
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_test.test_study_design FROM biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test JOIN biomarker_fda_test_trial AS biomarker_fda_test_trial ON biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trade_name JOIN disease AS disease ON biomarker_fda_test.doid = disease.id WHERE biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trial_id = "NCT01260168" and disease.name != "parathyroid carcinoma"

question: What are the different test design for FDA approved tests for prediction indication that are not the trial NCT01078662?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_test.test_study_design FROM biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test JOIN biomarker_fda_test_use AS biomarker_fda_test_use ON biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test_use.test_trade_name JOIN biomarker_fda_test_trial AS biomarker_fda_test_trial ON biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trade_name WHERE biomarker_fda_test_use.approved_indication = "prediction" and biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trial_id != "NCT01078662"

question: What are the descriptions for anatomical entities which are healthy exprions with expression level gene relative absence and stage name != "6 month-old stage (mouse)"?

question: Return the different anatomical entities's identifier which have both a QA state of Curated and an expression rank score higher than 92.20
query: SELECT DISTINCT anatomical_entity.uberon_identifier FROM anatomical_entity AS anatomical_entity JOIN biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn ON anatomical_entity.uberon_identifier = biomarker_edrn.uberon_anatomical_id JOIN healthy_expression AS healthy_expression ON anatomical_entity.uberon_identifier = healthy_expression.uberon_anatomical_id WHERE biomarker_edrn.qa_state = "Curated" and healthy_expression.expression_rank_score != 92.20

question: What are the expressions of call quality SILVER?
query: SELECT * FROM healthy_expression AS healthy_expression WHERE healthy_expression.call_quality = "SILVER"

question: List the description of the disease mutation site annotations whose disease mutation has a frequency of 15 and whose PMID is not 23014346

question: What are the distinct amino acid residue variations for disease mutations not named "blastoma"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT disease_mutation.amino_acid_residue_variation FROM disease_mutation AS disease_mutation JOIN disease_mutation_article AS disease_mutation_article ON disease_mutation.id = disease_mutation_article.disease_mutation_id JOIN disease AS disease ON disease_mutation.doid = disease.id WHERE disease_mutation_article.pmid = 11801303 and disease.name != "blastoma"

question: What is the different phases of the biomarker with id 699, which is not in the test submission P120014?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_edrn.phase FROM biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_edrn.id = biomarker.id JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker.id = biomarker_fda.id WHERE biomarker.biomarker_id = "urn:edrn:bmdb:biomarker:699" and biomarker_fda.test_submission != "P120014"

question: What test submissions exists for the biomarker RAB6B gene for drugs other than Erbitux (Cetuximab)?

question: What are the distinct tests that biomarker alias Beta-TG is a panel for, which have a different pmid than 17178863?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker.test_is_a_panel FROM biomarker AS biomarker JOIN biomarker_alias AS biomarker_alias ON biomarker.id = biomarker_alias.biomarker_internal_id JOIN biomarker_article AS biomarker_article ON biomarker.id = biomarker_article.biomarker_internal_id WHERE biomarker_alias.alias = "Beta-TG" and biomarker_article.pmid != "17178863"

question: How many subjects total have been tested for Malignant Mesothelioma using some test not called "VYSIS ALK Break Apart FISH Probe Kit"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT differential_expression.subjects_total FROM differential_expression AS differential_expression JOIN disease AS disease ON differential_expression.doid = disease.id JOIN biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test ON disease.id = biomarker_fda_test.doid WHERE disease.name = "malignant mesothelioma" and biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name != "VYSIS ALK Break Apart FISH Probe Kit"

question: List all drugs for FDA tests with submission P050045 S001-S004 whose biomarker origin is not Amplification.
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_drug FROM biomarker_fda_drug AS biomarker_fda_drug JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_fda_id = biomarker_fda.id JOIN biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test ON biomarker_fda.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name WHERE biomarker_fda.test_submission = "P050045 S001-S004" and biomarker_fda_test.biomarker_origin != "amplification"

question: What are the names of stages belonging to healthy gene expression levels and which do not correspond to gene symbol 1700025A08Rik?
query: SELECT DISTINCT stage.name FROM stage AS stage JOIN healthy_expression AS healthy_expression ON stage.id = healthy_expression.uberon_developmental_id JOIN xref_gene_ensembl AS xref_gene_ensembl ON healthy_expression.ensembl_gene_id = xref_gene_ensembl.ensembl_gene_id WHERE healthy_expression.expression_level_gene_relative = "LOW" and xref_gene_ensembl.gene_symbol != "1700025A08Rik"

question: List of FDA approved indications for test with histological type 8046 (Non-small cell carcinoma) not used in trials with id NCT00339183/NCT00079066.
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_test_use.approved_indication FROM biomarker_fda_test_use AS biomarker_fda_test_use JOIN biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test ON biomarker_fda_test_use.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name JOIN biomarker_fda_test_trial AS biomarker_fda_test_trial ON biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trade_name WHERE biomarker_fda_test.histological_type = "8046 (Non-small cell carcinoma)" and biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trial_id != "NCT00339183/NCT00079066"

question: Which mutations in the ICGC dataset not annotated for phosphothreonine by CDK1 and MAPK1 have site predictions?
query: SELECT DISTINCT disease_mutation_impact_prediction.site_prediction FROM disease_mutation_impact_prediction AS disease_mutation_impact_prediction JOIN disease_mutation AS disease_mutation ON disease_mutation_impact_prediction.disease_mutation_id = disease_mutation.id JOIN disease_mutation_site_annotation AS disease_mutation_site_annotation ON disease_mutation.id = disease_mutation_site_annotation.disease_mutation_id WHERE disease_mutation.data_source = "icgc" and disease_mutation_site_annotation.description != "Phosphothreonine; by CDK1 and MAPK1"

question: Show all QA state Curated biomarker_edrn.
query: SELECT * FROM biomarker_edrn AS biomarker_edrn WHERE biomarker_edrn.qa_state = "Curated"

question: What are the trade names of tests with FDA clinical significance "The therascreen KRAS RGQ PCR Kit is a real-time qualitative PCR assay used on the Rotor-Gene Q MDx instrument for the detection of seven somatic mutations in the human KRAS oncogene, using DNA extracted from formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE), colorectal cancer (CRC) tissue." that are not part of trial NCT01153763?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda.test_trade_name FROM biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda JOIN biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test ON biomarker_fda.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name JOIN biomarker_fda_test_trial AS biomarker_fda_test_trial ON biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trade_name WHERE biomarker_fda_test.clinical_significance = "The therascreen KRAS RGQ PCR Kit is a real-time qualitative PCR assay used on the Rotor-Gene Q MDx instrument for the detection of seven somatic mutations in the human KRAS oncogene, using DNA extracted from formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE), colorectal cancer (CRC) tissue." and biomarker_fda_test_trial.test_trial_id != "NCT01153763"

question: What are the actual uses of FDA test with number of genes 3 and trade name not equal to "Oncomine Dx Target Test"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_test_use.actual_use FROM biomarker_fda_test_use AS biomarker_fda_test_use JOIN biomarker_fda_test AS biomarker_fda_test ON biomarker_fda_test_use.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker_fda_test.test_trade_name = biomarker_fda.test_trade_name WHERE biomarker_fda_test.test_number_genes = 3 and biomarker_fda.test_trade_name != "Oncomine Dx Target Test"

question: What are the distinct disease ontology identifiers for disease mutations with site predictions "+++|gain" and whose feature key is not "modified residue"?
query: SELECT DISTINCT disease_mutation.disease_ontology_identifier FROM disease_mutation AS disease_mutation JOIN disease_mutation_impact_prediction AS disease_mutation_impact_prediction ON disease_mutation.id = disease_mutation_impact_prediction.disease_mutation_id JOIN disease_mutation_site_annotation AS disease_mutation_site_annotation ON disease_mutation.id = disease_mutation_site_annotation.disease_mutation_id WHERE disease_mutation_impact_prediction.site_prediction = "+++|gain" and disease_mutation_site_annotation.feature_key != "modified residue"

question: What FDA drugs contain the biomarker THXID-BRAF KIT and do not have the description WWC1, or KIBRA, is a cytoplasmic phosphoprotein. Expression has been detected in the brain, heart, colon and kidney, as well as mammary epithelial cells and breast cancer cell lines. WWC1 interacts with PRKC-zeta and dynein light chain-1. Alleles of this gene have been found that may be associated with memory performance. Three transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been found for the WWC1 gene.
query: SELECT DISTINCT biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_drug FROM biomarker_fda_drug AS biomarker_fda_drug JOIN biomarker_fda AS biomarker_fda ON biomarker_fda_drug.biomarker_fda_id = biomarker_fda.id JOIN biomarker AS biomarker ON biomarker_fda.id = biomarker.id WHERE biomarker_fda.test_trade_name = "THXID-BRAF KIT" and biomarker.biomarker_description != "WWC1, or KIBRA, is a cytoplasmic phosphoprotein.  Expression has been detected in the brain, heart, colon and kidney, as well as mammary epithelial cells and breast cancer cell lines.  WWC1 interacts with PRKC-zeta and dynein light chain-1. Alleles of this gene have been found that may be associated with memory performance. Three transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been found for the WWC1 gene."

question: What are the subjects without coverage for germ cell cancer mutations?

question: What are the distinct FDA test trial ids that do not correspond to the clinical significance "The THxIDTM BRAF kit is an In Vitro Diagnostic device intended for the qualitative detection of the BRAF V600E and V600K mutations in DNA samples extracted from formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) human melanoma tissue" and that are not for "prognostic predictive" use?
